  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to:\n\n1. Identify and verify customer identities\n2. Monitor transactions for suspicious activity\n3. Report suspicious transactions to financial intelligence units\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Implement internal anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n\nSpecific reporting requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve filing suspicious activity reports (SARs) with appropriate authorities.",
